---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof vs Tally — Testimonial collection done right | SocialProof" description="Tally is a beautiful form builder but it doesn't display testimonials. SocialProof collects and embeds testimonials in one tool. Free to start." canonical="https://socialproof.dev/vs/tally">
<style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; margin: 0; background: #fff; color: #111; }
    nav { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; }
    nav a.logo { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #111; text-decoration: none; }
    nav .nav-links a { margin-left: 1.5rem; color: #555; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    nav .cta-nav { background: #111; color: #fff !important; padding: .45rem 1rem; border-radius: 6px; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .vs-badge { display: inline-block; background: #f0f0f0; color: #555; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .35rem .75rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .hero h1 span { color: #4f46e5; }
    .hero p { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #444; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .hero-cta { display: inline-block; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
    .hero-cta:hover { background: #3730a3; }
    .price-callout { display: inline-flex; gap: 2rem; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .price-callout .item { text-align: center; }
    .price-callout .item .price { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; }
    .price-callout .item .label { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #777; margin-top: .2rem; }
    .price-callout .item.vouch .price { color: #4f46e5; }
    .price-callout .item.other .price { color: #dc2626; }
    section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .compare-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .compare-table th { padding: .75rem 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .05em; color: #888; border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; }
    .compare-table th:nth-child(2) { color: #4f46e5; }
    .compare-table td { padding: .85rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; font-size: 0.97rem; vertical-align: top; }
    .compare-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .compare-table td:first-child { color: #555; font-weight: 500; }
    .yes { color: #16a34a; font-weight: 600; }
    .no { color: #dc2626; font-weight: 600; }
    .partial { color: #d97706; font-weight: 600; }
    .winner-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .winner-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.75rem; }
    .winner-card.vouch { background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #86efac; }
    .winner-card.other { background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; }
    .winner-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 .75rem; }
    .winner-card ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
    .winner-card li { font-size: 0.92rem; color: #444; margin-bottom: .4rem; }
    .savings-box { background: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fcd34d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .savings-box h3 { margin: 0 0 .5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
    .savings-box p { margin: 0; color: #555; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .bottom-cta { text-align: center; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 3.5rem 2rem; margin: 3rem 0; }
    .bottom-cta h2 { color: #fff; font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .bottom-cta p { color: #c7d2fe; max-width: 500px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .bottom-cta a { display: inline-block; background: #fff; color: #4f46e5; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
    footer { text-align: center; padding: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; color: #aaa; font-size: 0.85rem; }
    footer a { color: #aaa; margin: 0 .5rem; }
    @media (max-width: 600px) { .winner-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .price-callout { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; } }
</style>
<nav>
  <a href="/" class="logo">SocialProof</a>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="/vs">Compare</a>
    <a href="/for">Industries</a>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="cta-nav">Try free →</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <span class="vs-badge">SocialProof vs Tally</span>
  <h1>Beautiful form. Then <span>what?</span></h1>
  <p>Tally makes gorgeous forms — but after a customer submits a testimonial, it lives in Tally's inbox. SocialProof takes it further: approve it, embed it, done.</p>
  <div class="price-callout">
    <div class="item vouch">
      <div class="price">Free</div>
      <div class="label">SocialProof — collect + display</div>
    </div>
    <div class="item other">
      <div class="price">$29/mo</div>
      <div class="label">Tally Pro (remove branding)</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="hero-cta">Try SocialProof free →</a>
</div>

<section>
  <h2>Side-by-side comparison</h2>
  <table class="compare-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Feature</th>
        <th>SocialProof</th>
        <th>Tally</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Primary purpose</td>
        <td class="yes">Testimonial collection + display</td>
        <td class="partial">General form builder</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Free plan</td>
        <td class="yes">Free forever — 1 widget, no branding</td>
        <td class="partial">Free — with Tally branding on forms</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Embeddable testimonial widget</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes — copy one script tag</td>
        <td class="no">No — responses stay in Tally</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Testimonial approval before publish</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes — built-in</td>
        <td class="no">No — no approval workflow</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Structured star ratings</td>
        <td class="yes">Built-in, automatically formatted</td>
        <td class="partial">Manual opinion scale field</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Remove branding on free plan</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes</td>
        <td class="no">$29/mo Tally Pro required</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Display on your website</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes — automatic</td>
        <td class="no">Requires Zapier or custom code</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Purpose-built testimonial UX</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes — guided, conversion-optimized</td>
        <td class="partial">Generic form experience</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Pricing for small businesses</td>
        <td class="yes">$0–$9/mo</td>
        <td class="no">$0 (branded) or $29/mo</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Tally is great at forms. Testimonials need more.</h2>
  <p style="color:#444; line-height:1.7;">Tally has a genuinely lovely form-building experience — minimalist, fast, Notion-inspired. For collecting survey responses or contact forms, it's excellent. But a testimonial system needs more than a collection endpoint:</p>
  <ul style="color:#444; line-height:1.8; margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;">
    <li><strong>Curation:</strong> You need to review and approve what shows publicly</li>
    <li><strong>Display:</strong> The testimonials need to actually appear on your site</li>
    <li><strong>Context:</strong> Name, photo, star rating, company — structured automatically</li>
    <li><strong>Continuity:</strong> New testimonials auto-populate as you approve them</li>
  </ul>
  <p style="color:#444; line-height:1.7;">None of these are in Tally's scope. They're exactly SocialProof's core.</p>

  <div class="winner-grid">
    <div class="winner-card vouch">
      <h3>✅ Choose SocialProof when you need to…</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Show testimonials on your website automatically</li>
        <li>Approve before anything goes public</li>
        <li>Start for free without your tool's branding in the form</li>
        <li>Skip the Zapier / custom code setup</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="winner-card other">
      <h3>📋 Stick with Tally if you…</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Need complex multi-step forms beyond testimonials</li>
        <li>Love Notion-style minimal form UX for other uses</li>
        <li>Already use Tally for other forms and want consistency</li>
        <li>Have a developer who can build the display layer</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="savings-box">
    <h3>💡 Free vs free — but for different things</h3>
    <p>Both Tally and SocialProof have free plans. The difference: SocialProof's free plan includes the display widget. Tally's free plan collects data but keeps it in Tally — and charges $29/mo to even remove their branding. If you want testimonials on your website, SocialProof's free plan does more.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="bottom-cta">
    <h2>From "collected" to "on your site" in 2 minutes.</h2>
    <p>SocialProof handles collection and display together. Free forever for 1 active widget.</p>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup">Get started free →</a>
  </div>
</section>

<footer>
  <a href="/">SocialProof</a>
  <a href="/vs">All comparisons</a>
  <a href="/for">Industries</a>
  <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
  <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
  <p style="margin-top:1rem;">© 2025 SocialProof. Free testimonial tool for small businesses.</p>
</footer>

<div class="footer-links" style="margin-top:2rem;padding-top:1.5rem;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:0.9rem;">
  <strong style="color:#374151;">Also explore:</strong>
  <a href="/for/coaches" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Coaches</a>
  <a href="/for/freelancers" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Freelancers</a>
  <a href="/for/ecommerce" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Ecommerce</a>
  <a href="/vs/senja" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">vs Senja</a>
  <a href="/vs/testimonial" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">vs Testimonial.to</a>
</div>
</Base>
